% Section 2.3.4 close-out: a parse error inside a `presburger "..."`
% literal must attribute its position to the literal's column on the
% source line, not the placeholder `(0,0)-(0,0)`.  Here the
% literal is malformed (unbalanced parenthesis), so loading must fail
% with an install-pass error whose location includes the literal's
% line and column from `test/sloc/install_pass_loc.hol`.
type checkBad o.
checkBad :- presburger "(X = 1".
